    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-centre-and-angle-of-rotation">
        <title>Centre and Angle of Rotation</title>

        <activity>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work in pairs.
                </p>

                <p>
                    In the figures below, the triangle <m>X'Y'Z'</m> is the image of triangle <m>XYZ</m> after rotation. Find the centre and angle of rotation
                </p>

                    <image source="/image-object-triangle1.png">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                <p>
                    In order to determine the centre and angle of rotation we have to follow the following steps:
                </p>

                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Trace the figure. Join <m>Z</m> to <m>Z'</m> and construct a perpendicular bisector to <m>ZZ''</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                 Join <m>Y</m> to <m>Y'</m> and construct a perpendicular bisector to <m>YY'</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Also you can join <m>X</m> to <m>X'</m> and construct a perpendicular bisector to <m>XX'</m>
                            </p>

                            <p>
                               The point where the perpendicular lines intersect is the centre of rotation.. 
                            </p>
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Join <m>O</m> to <m>Z</m> and <m>Z'</m>. Measure <m>\angle\, ZOZ'</m>. This is the <m>{\color{black} \text{angle of rotation}}</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>{\color{black} \text{Note:}}</m>
                </p>

                <p>
                    <m>\angle\, ZOZ' = \angle\, YOY' = \angle\, XOX'</m>
                </p>

                    <image source="/centre-angle-enlargement.png">
                        <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    </image>

                    <p>
                        Triangle <m>X'Y'Z'</m> is the image of triangle <m>XYZ</m> under a rotation through <m>120^\circ</m> in anticlockwise direction
                    </p>

             </statement>
        </activity>
        
